The Sanzang asked for a lamp and went to bed in the front meditation hall as before
The monks all slept under thatched shelters rigged up against the walls leaving the abbot's quarters at the back for the senior and junior prelate
It was a peaceful night The Milky Way was clear The jade firmament free of dust
The sky was full of coruscating stars A single wave wiped out the traces
Stilled were all sounds And the birds were silent on a thousand hills
