When Pig saw the great yellow hurricane blow up and cast Heaven and Earth into darkness he held on to the horse and kept a grip on the carrying pole while he crouched in the hollow on the mountain side not daring to open his eyes or raise his head as he invoked the Buddha and made all sorts of vows to him
