Even if it doesn't kill you you'll have tetanus for the rest of your days The ogre dropped his defensive posture and fought with Pig from the riverbed to the surface of the water
This battle was fiercer than the earlier ones The precious staff whirled The deadly rake struck And no word passed between the two foes
Because the Mother of Wood conquered the Medicine Measure The pair of them had to fight each other twice
With no victory And no defeat The waves were overturned and knew no peace
How could the one hold back his anger How could the other bear his humiliation
As the staff parried the rake's blows they showed their prowess Each was most vicious as the Flowing Sands River rolled
Towering rage Strenuous efforts All because Sanzang wanted to go West
The rake was thoroughly murderous The staff was wielded with experience
