All those Buddhist monks were presented to us by His Majesty Even if we released just one or two of them we'd have to cover up by handing in sick notes for them to our masters then filling out death certificates We couldn't possibly release the whole lot of them
It would be outrageous quite outrageous
We'd have no servants and the king would be very angry with us
The ward head is always sending officials to check up and sometimes the king even comes to count them himself
We couldn't possibly let them go You couldn't said Monkey
No the priests replied
By the time he had asked this and been given the same answer three times he was in a terrible rage He produced his iron cudgel from his ear created a spell with his hands made it as thick as a rice bowl swung it and brought it down on the Taoists' faces
